		<li><strong>Best application:</strong> Long-term installations, high-visibility areas</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Critical Vinyl Installation Considerations</h3>
	<p>Proper installation is crucial for vinyl performance in Stockton:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Expansion gaps:</strong> Must allow 1/4-1/2 inch for thermal expansion</li>
		<li><strong>Reinforcement:</strong> Metal reinforcement essential for gates and high-wind areas</li>
		<li><strong>Post depth:</strong> Deep concrete footings prevent wind damage</li>
		<li><strong>Quality fasteners:</strong> Use vinyl-specific screws that allow movement</li>
		<li><strong>UV-rated materials:</strong> Ensure all components are UV-stabilized</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Metal Fencing in Stockton's Climate</h2>

	<h3>Aluminum Fencing Performance</h3>
	<p>Aluminum offers unique advantages for Central Valley conditions:</p>

	<p><strong>Advantages in Our Climate:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>No rust:</strong> Aluminum naturally resists corrosion in all weather</li>
		<li><strong>Minimal expansion:</strong> Handles temperature extremes without warping</li>
		<li><strong>Low maintenance:</strong> Powder coating lasts 10-15 years without touch-up</li>
		<li><strong>Wind resistant:</strong> Open design reduces wind load significantly</li>
		<li><strong>Long lifespan:</strong> 20-25 years typical with minimal maintenance</li>
		<li><strong>Lightweight:</strong> Easier installation, less stress on posts</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Challenges in Our Climate:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Heat conduction:</strong> Gets very hot in summer sun (150°F+ surface temp)</li>
		<li><strong>No privacy:</strong> Open design doesn't block views or sound</li>
		<li><strong>Impact damage:</strong> Can dent if struck by equipment or vehicles</li>
		<li><strong>Cost:</strong> Higher upfront investment than wood</li>
		<li><strong>Limited styles:</strong> Mostly decorative picket designs available</li>
	</ul>

