	<h2>Making the Right Choice for Your Stockton Property</h2>

	<h3>Choose Wood If:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>You want traditional aesthetic appeal and warmth</li>
		<li>Budget is tight for initial installation</li>
		<li>You don't mind regular maintenance tasks</li>
		<li>You plan to paint or stain in custom colors</li>
		<li>Privacy is your primary concern</li>
		<li>You're comfortable with 10-15 year replacement cycle</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Choose Vinyl If:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Minimal maintenance is a priority</li>
		<li>You want maximum privacy with longevity</li>
		<li>You can afford higher upfront investment</li>
		<li>Your property has challenging exposure (full sun)</li>
		<li>You prefer modern, clean appearance</li>
		<li>You want 20-30 year fence lifespan</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Choose Aluminum If:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>You need decorative appearance without privacy</li>
		<li>Low maintenance is important</li>
		<li>Wind resistance is a concern (exposed lots)</li>
		<li>You want pool fencing that meets safety codes</li>
		<li>Rust-free performance is essential</li>
		<li>Your property has high visibility frontage</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Choose Wrought Iron If:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>Security is your primary concern</li>
		<li>You want maximum curb appeal and property value</li>
		<li>Budget allows for premium investment</li>
		<li>You're willing to maintain coating/paint</li>
		<li>You have heritage or high-end property</li>
		<li>Longevity justifies higher cost</li>
	</ul>

